{"questionId":"9076451","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A cylinder is fitted with a piston. A fixed mass of an ideal gas fills the space above the piston.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4756/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-12_om_16.52.30.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP3/ENG/TZ2/07._01\"></p>\n<p>The gas expands isobarically. The following data are available.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"mjpage mjpage__block\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\" alttext=\"\\begin{array}{*{20}{l}} {{\\text{Amount of gas}}}&amp;{ = 243{\\text{ mol}}} \\\\ {{\\text{Initial volume of gas}}}&amp;{ = 47.1{\\text{ }}{{\\text{m}}^3}} \\\\ {{\\text{Initial temperature of gas}}}&amp;{ = -12.0{\\text{ °C}}} \\\\ {{\\text{Final temperature of gas}}}&amp;{ = + 19.0{\\text{ °C}}} \\\\ {{\\text{Initial pressure of gas}}}&amp;{ = 11.2{\\text{ kPa}}} \\end{array}\">\n  <mtable columnalign=\"left\" rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>Amount of gas</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>243</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>&nbsp;mol</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>Initial volume of gas</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>47.1</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>&nbsp;</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mrow>\n                <mtext>m</mtext>\n              </mrow>\n              <mn>3</mn>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>Initial temperature of gas</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>12.0</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>&nbsp;°C</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>Final temperature of gas</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>19.0</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>&nbsp;°C</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>Initial pressure of gas</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>11.2</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>&nbsp;kPa</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n  </mtable>\n</math></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate, in J, the work done by the gas during this expansion.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>W</em>&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>=&nbsp;<em>P</em>Δ<em>V</em><strong>»</strong> = 11.2&nbsp;× 10<sup>3</sup>&nbsp;× (52.7 – 47.1)</p>\n<p><em>W</em> = 62.7&nbsp;× 10<sup>3</sup>&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>J<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Accept 66.1 × 10<sup>3</sup>&nbsp;J if 53 used</em></p>\n<p><em>Accept 61.6 × 10<sup>3</sup>&nbsp;J if 52.6&nbsp;used</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076451","referenceCode":"18M.3.SL.TZ2.7b","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate, in J, the work done by the gas during this expansion.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Core topics)","B.2 – Thermodynamics","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}